      <description><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/DWIljUBj7Yk/"><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/655169818_18573989134057657_5179003135457244956_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_p360x360_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=107&amp;ig_cache_key=Mzg1NzQ5ODIzNTI0NjQ1ODQwNDE4NTczOTg5MTMxMDU3NjU3.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjc3MngxMzY2LnNkci5DMyJ9&amp;_nc_ohc=-t9AEKY8lMMQ7kNvwGKrftb&amp;_nc_oc=Adp1eoMAVSYajmfhM2Rd5WVzbBlc6i1Px2r28T93IL8bPRcmY9_WVPfjurajVXjuVN8&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=GCgtaz0X52u2tt1KhBm9ug&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_Afw22fV8YlLAhYPCjkC_p5xYhUn0CoM7p73aO4WlU1Pzmg&amp;oe=69CA1DBB" alt="Video-thumbnail fra @sofiedirksgottlieb" /></a></p><p><strong>🎬 Video</strong></p><p><strong>@sofiedirksgottlieb</strong></p><p>NOW OPEN | HYBRID FUTURES - RHODA TING &amp; MIKKEL BOJESEN <br/>
<br/>
HYBRID FUTURES was officially opened by H.M. King Frederik X with H.M Queen Mary of Denmark on Wednesday 18 March <br/>
<br/>
HYBRID FUTURES marks the first solo exhibition in Australia by Rhoda Ting (b. 1985, Australia) and Mikkel Bojesen (b. 1988, Denmark), an artist duo based between Melbourne and Copenhagen. Born on opposite sides of the world, their collaborative practice examines how life is continuously shaped through human, technological, and industrial relations. The exhibition proposes that hybridity, the mixing and merging of things we once thought separate, is not something arriving in the future. It is already the condition of the world we live in.<br/>
<br/>
This significant exhibition brings together sculpture, film, photography, and living installations to explore the porous intersections of biology, industry, and technology. Just as the artists themselves move between Australia and Denmark, many of the works are made across both countries, drawing on the distinct landscapes, coastlines, and ecologies of each to examine what is shared, entangled, and co-evolving between them.<br/>
<br/>
The exhibition is co-curated by Sally Dan-Cuthbert (Sydney) and Sofie Dirks Gottlieb (Copenhagen).<br/>
<br/>
Hybrid Futures is supported with funds from a joint grant under the Danish Ministry of Culture and the Ministry of Foreign Aﬀairs of Denmark and Artbank Australia. <br/>
